        "textColor": "#000000",
        "label": "Every invoice is different.  If you are entering items from an invoice where the whole invoice is for one job, but multiple items, enter the freight as a separate entry.  \nIf there is only one item for one job, you can add the freight cost to the total item cost and then divide by the number of items to come up with the “Per Item Cost”.\nIf there is one item but it is being divided between multiple jobs, divide the items and cost for each job, then take a percentage of the freight for each job based on what percent each job is to the total invoice , divide it by the number of items, and then add it to the item cost for that job.",
        "ddrArrangeOrder": 28
      },
      "type": "label"
    },
